msgstr "Героям слава!"

#: assets/maps/level.tmx//map/objectgroup/object[@id=8419]
msgid "this sign has{{BR}}SHARP EDGES{{BR}}do not touch"
msgstr "tällä kyltillä on{{BR}}TERÄVÄT REUNAT{{BR}}älä koske"

#: assets/maps/level.tmx//map/objectgroup/object[@id=8423]
msgid "A path to another world has appeared nearby."
msgstr "Toiseen maailmaan on avautunut reitti lähellä."

#: assets/maps/level.tmx//map/objectgroup/object[@id=8439]
msgid "You can now enter another world!"
msgstr "Voit nyt astua toiseen maailmaan!"

#: assets/maps/level.tmx//map/objectgroup/object[@id=8441]
msgid "The Teleporter{{BR}}(press {{ExitButton}})"
msgstr "Teleportteri{{BR}}(paina {{ExitButton}})"

#. This is a reference to SheetMusicBoss's song "Rush E". Try making a pun
#. based on Rush E, or an arbitrary reference to SheetMusicBoss, I guess. Or
#. one of the common YT comments on those videos of the sort "I paid for the
#. whole piano, I'm gonna use the whole piano".
#: assets/maps/level.tmx//map/objectgroup/object[@id=8539]
msgid "Why the rush, eh?"
msgstr "En soita pianoa, piano soittaa minuE."

#. This is a reference to Beethoven's Für Elise. If there's a common
#. misspelling in your language, make a pun based on it; otherwise, maybe
#. comment on how overplayed it is, or on Beethoven's hearing?
#: assets/maps/level.tmx//map/objectgroup/object[@id=8541]
msgid "She's no furry - that letter is an \"ü\"!"
msgstr "Beethoven: olen säveltäjä{{BR}}Kuurous: ei{{BR}}Beethoven: joo"

#. Comic explosion sign.
#: assets/maps/level.tmx//map/objectgroup/object[@id=8543]
msgid "Bang!"
msgstr "Pam!"

#: assets/maps/level.tmx//map/objectgroup/object[@id=8543]
msgid "I think you meant to play{{BR}}In the Hall of the Mountain King?"
msgstr "Sinun olisi kai pitänyt{{BR}}soittaa Vuorenkuninkaan luolaa?"

#. Reference to Super Mario 64's intro letter from Princess Peach, combined
#. with the wellknown phrase misattributed to Marie Antoinette. Try finding
#. both phrases as most commonly used in your language in the given contexts
#. and use those. Definitely don't reference Portal here - let's not overdo
#. those. If Asterix is well-known in your culture, you may consider making it
#. an "arsenic cake"; if not, reference Grieg's In the Hall of the Mountain
#. King.
#: assets/maps/level.tmx//map/objectgroup/object[@id=8556]
msgid ""
"Dear Mario:{{BR}}Please come to the castle.{{BR}}Let them eat "
"cake...{{BR}}Arsenic cake?"
msgstr ""
"Rakas Mario:{{BR}}Sinut on kutsuttu linnaan.{{BR}}Anna heidän syödä "
"kakkua...{{BR}}Myrkkykakkua?"

#: assets/maps/level.tmx//map/objectgroup/object[@id=8557]
msgid "I think you meant to play{{BR}}Arsenic Cake?"
msgstr "Sinun olisi kai pitänyt soittaa{{BR}}myrkkykakkua?"

#. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ReblZ7o7lu4 - however, feel free to put in
